===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|obsolete}} a [[fence]] or railing surrounding a [[well]]; a [[puteal]]
# {{lb|zh|historical}} Han, a minor state enfeoffed by the Zhou dynasty, later destroyed by Jin
#* {{zh-x|韓侯 受命，王 親 命 之。|The Marquis of Han received the mandate; the king personally charged him with it.|ref=Shijing, “Han Yi”|CL}}
# {{lb|zh|historical}} Han, one of the [[Seven Warring States]], later conquered by Qin in 230 BCE
#* {{zh-x|李斯 因 說 秦王，請 先 取 韓 以 恐 他國，於是 使 斯 下 韓。|Li Si thereupon persuaded the king of Qin, asking him to take Han first in order to intimidate the other states; the king then sent Li Si to subdue Han.|ref=Shiji|CL}}
# {{lb|zh|astronomy}} the star [[w:Zeta Ophiuchi|Zeta Ophiuchi]] in traditional Chinese astronomy, named after the state
#: {{syn|zh|天市右垣十一}}
# {{lb|zh|historical}} [[Samhan]], the three ancient confederacies of Mahan, Byeonhan, and Jinhan in the southern Korean Peninsula
# {{lb|zh|historical}} Korea; specifically, the [[w:Korean Empire|Korean Empire]] from 1897 to 1910; {{zh-short|大韓帝國}}
# {{zh-short|韓國|[[Korea]], especially [[South Korea]]}}
#: {{zh-x|中日韓|China, Japan and Korea}}
# {{surname|zh}}
#: {{zh-x|韓愈|{{w|Han Yu}} {{gloss|Tang-dynasty writer and official}}}}

